value.value: Liquid preparation consisting of a solution intended for use in the preparation of a spray.

label.value: Solution for Suspension for Injection Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of a solution intended for use in the preparation of a suspension for injection.

label.value: Solution for Use in Drinking Water Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation for veterinary use consisting of a solution intended for administration by incorporation into the animal drinking water. If direct oral administration to individual animals is also authorized, the method of administration, including any necessary dilution, is clearly described in the product information.

label.value: Solution for Use in Drinking Water/Milk Dosage Form

value.value: Solution for veterinary use, intended for administration by incorporation into the animal drinking water, milk or milk replacer. If direct oral administration to individual animals is also authorized, the method of administration, including any necessary dilution, is clearly described in the product information.

label.value: Solvent for Parenteral Use Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of a solvent containing no active substances, intended for use in the preparation of a product for parenteral use.

label.value: Solvent for Solution for Infusion Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of a solvent containing no active substances, intended for use in the preparation of a solution for infusion.

label.value: Solvent for Solution for Intraocular Irrigation Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of a solvent containing no active substances, intended for use in the preparation of a solution for intraocular irrigation.

Liquid preparation consisting of an excipient that contains no active substances itself but is intended to be used in the preparation of a pharmaceutical product, e.g. for diluting/dissolving/dispersing the item(s) containing the active substance(s).
Administration device with a flattened side used for the application of semi-solid pharmaceutical forms.
A unit of presentation used to represent the quantity of product that is administered by filling a single spoon administration device.
Device for administration by spot-on use.

Liquid preparation consisting of an emulsion intended for spot-on use for the prevention and treatment of ectoparasitic and/or endoparasitic infestations of animals. Spot-on-emulsions are applied in volumes that are usually less than 10 mL.

Liquid preparation consisting of a solution intended for spot-on use for the prevention and treatment of ectoparasitic and/or endoparasitic infestations of animals. Spot-on-solutions are applied in volumes that are usually less than 10 mL.

Liquid preparation consisting of a suspension intended for spot-on use for the prevention and treatment of ectoparasitic and/or endoparasitic infestations of animals. Spot-on-suspensions are applied in volumes that are usually less than 10 mL.
Administration of a veterinary medicinal product to a single site on the back of the animal or the base of the poll of the head.
Container for a liquid pharmaceutical form to be converted into a spray by mechanical means.
A valve device on a container that delivers a precise spray dose of contents by actuation.

The technique of administration of a pharmaceutical product by atomizing or otherwise dissipating it into a fine dispersion of particles in air, directing it such that it comes into contact with the affected area.
Device for administering a product by stabbing the bird.
Liquid sterile preparation consisting of an aqueous solution intended for irrigation of the stomach.
Hollow tube containing a single dose of a medicinal product for oral administration by sucking.
A unit of presentation used to represent the quantity of product that is found in a single straw container.
Solid preparation consisting of a single- or multilayer sheet of suitable material(s) intended for sublingual use to obtain a systemic effect.
Solid preparation consisting of a powder intended for sublingual use.
Liquid, usually multidose preparation consisting of an emulsion intended for sublingual use. Sublingual sprays are usually presented in pressurized containers with a metering valve.
Liquid, usually multidose preparation consisting of a solution intended for sublingual use. Sublingual sprays are usually presented in pressurized containers with a metering valve.
Liquid, usually multidose preparation consisting of a suspension intended for sublingual use. Sublingual sprays are usually presented in pressurized containers with a metering valve.
The technique of administration of a pharmaceutical product by placing it in the mouth and encouraging it to dissolve in the saliva, usually by moving the tongue.

label.value: Suspension and Effervescent Granules for Oral Suspension Dosage Form

value.value: Suspension and effervescent granules intended for the preparation of an oral suspension by dissolving or dispersing the effervescent granules in the suspension, or by dissolving or dispersing the effervescent granules in the specified liquid and mixing it with the suspension. The suspension contains active ingredient(s); the effervescent granules do not contain active ingredient(s).

label.value: Suspension and Solution for Spray Dosage Form

value.value: Suspension and solution intended for use as a spray by mixing the suspension into the solution.

label.value: Injectable Suspension for Emulsion Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of a suspension intended for use in the preparation of an emulsion for injection.

label.value: Suspension for Injection in Cartridge Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of a suspension for injection presented in a cartridge.

label.value: Suspension for Injection in Pre-filled Injector Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of a suspension for injection presented in a pre-filled injector.

label.value: Suspension for Injection in Pre-filled Pen Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of a suspension for injection presented in a pre-filled pen.

label.value: Suspension for Injection in Pre-filled Syringe Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of a suspension for injection presented in a pre-filled syringe.

Suspension for Oral Suspension Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation consisting of a suspension intended for use in the preparation of an oral suspension.

label.value: Suspension for Suspension for Injection Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of a suspension intended for use in the preparation of a suspension for injection.

label.value: Suspension for Use in Drinking Water Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation for veterinary use consisting of a suspension intended for administration by incorporation into the animal drinking water. If direct oral administration to individual animals is also authorized, the method of administration, including any necessary dilution, is clearly described in the product information.
The technique of administration of a pharmaceutical product by introducing it into the stomach via the mouth and esophagus with a voluntary muscular action.
Medicinal product consisting of a syrup in a sachet.
A unit of presentation used to represent the quantity of product that is found in a single discrete entity where the pharmaceutical dose form is a type of system.

label.value: Tablet plus Vaginal Tablet Dosage Form

value.value: Combination package consisting of a tablet and a vaginal tablet.

label.value: Tablet and Powder for Oral Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Tablet and powder intended for the preparation of an oral solution by dissolving the tablet and the powder in the specified liquid. The tablet contains active ingredient(s); the powder does not contain active ingredient(s).

label.value: Tablet and Solvent for Rectal Suspension Dosage Form

value.value: Tablet and solvent intended for the preparation of a rectal suspension by dispersing the tablet in the solvent.
Container without neck and with a flat bottom, suited for tablets, capsules, etc., can be re-closed well.
